# Project Overview

This is an **Electron desktop application** with an **Angular client**.

## Structure

- **Root** — the Electron app.
  - `main.js`: Electron entry point. Loads the built UI from `./build/index.html`.
  - `package.json`: Electron app manifest. `npm start` runs Electron; `npm run build-client` builds the Angular client.
- **`client/`** — the Angular client (Angular + Angular Material).
  - Source lives in `client/src/`; static assets in `client/public/`.
  - `client/angular.json` is configured to build into the top-level `build/` folder with `baseHref: "./"` so assets resolve under Electron's `file://` protocol.
- **`build/`** — generated output from the Angular build. Do not edit by hand; it is regenerated by `npm run build-client`.
